Petrol will drop by 69 cents, diesel by 60 cents and illuminating paraffin will go down by 76 cents a litre. JOHANNESBURG - The price of petrol will drop by 69 cents a litre at midnight, while diesel will go down by 60 cents.The Energy Department says the strengthening of the rand against the US dollar has helped.Illuminating paraffin will go down by 76 cents a litre.The Automobile Association's Layton Beard says future predictions of the fuel price remain difficult in the current environment of political instability and he has urged motorists to save while they can. Any saving that they can realise now, I think should be kept in reserve for those months when the petrol price may increase again. 